{{Quote|There's a lot of rumors floating around the Deep Core, from tales of the Emperor's hidden pleasure palace to stories about that so-called Citadel Inquisitorius that I don't even feel comfortable talking about on a private shadowfeed.|[[Amara (information broker)|Amara]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Force and Destiny Core Rulebook">[[Star Wars: Force and Destiny Core Rulebook|''Star Wars: Force and Destiny'' Core Rulebook]]</ref>}}
'''Citadel Inquisitorius''' was the headquarters for most of the [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitorius]], located on the [[Mountain/Legends|mountainous]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Prakith/Legends|Prakith]] in the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]]. Here, the [[High Inquisitor]]s received assignments and conferred with other Inquisitors. The citadel was a dark, fear-inspiring tower jutting forebodingly from the mountains. Inside, it had features similar to those of religious structures found [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxywide]], with vaulted ceilings and massive [[Obsidian/Legends|obsidian]] columns; it also contained a number of [[Prison/Legends|detention cells]] and [[Torture/Legends|torture]] chambers used to interrogate the most resilient and dangerous [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]].

Many Prakith citizens claimed that the screams of tortured [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] brought to the citadel echoed across the mountains for [[Standard day/Legends|days]] on end.

==History==
Circa [[17 BBY/Legends|17 BBY]], [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Denia]] was [[Battle of the Resurgence|captured]] by her former [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]], [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] Inquisitor [[Valin Draco]]. She was held deep within the Citadel Inquisitorius on Pakith and tortured. Her allies in the [[Alderaanian Resistance]] later tried to [[Mission to Prakith (Imperial Period)|rescue]] her by attacking the Citadel, but she sacrificed herself during the battle to allow the Rebels to escape.<ref name="SotE">{{DoD|Sword of the Empire}}</ref>

